+fn output_guard_guidance() -> &'static str {
+    "- Protect the UI from accidental output floods with a command-side limit before output reaches the tool. Choose the limiter by intent: use `sed -n '1,200p' file` for a specific file range, `head -n 40 file` for a small file prefix, `cmd | head -n 200` for line-oriented search/list output, and `cmd | head -c 12000` when line width is unknown or output may contain very long lines. `max_output_tokens` only limits the tool response returned to the model; it is not a substitute for capping command output in the shell. If you need a complete file, do not read only the first lines as a shortcut; first confirm the file is small enough or read it in bounded chunks."
+}
